column2: IF TP  more than  0.2 RUN AT HIGH LEVEL
Partly cloudy- small chop.  No weeds observed.
Partly cloudy and a nice chop on the lake.
Sunny and a little chop on the water

Party sunny/cloudy- mild. Bald Eagle activity continues in current nest located just off "deep hole" in small bay. Two large juveniles occupy nest. Adults hunting nearby. Pair of loons in bay today coming near my pontoon. Beautiful! Have noticed loons show virtually no fear of boats especially last two summers. Several loons occupy Hart Lake.
1 of 2 juvenile bald eagles out of nest- and perched on  branch of 1st tree just east of nest tree. It is perched approx. 10-15 feet below nest height on small branch. No adults in area at this time.
Group of 5 adult loons in close proximity fishing together just out past my dock. Also- group of 3 otters fishing just off my dock.
Several adult loons present on Hart Lake- no chicks sighted. Bald Eagle nest still occupied by 2 juveniles occasionally- as they are now both flying on their own with parents in close proximity.
Mild- low 70's- partly sunny. Two juvenile loons- and one immature bald eagle spotted today. Eagle was perched at nest site. No adults in sight at this time.
